  "title": "Urgent! Regional Segment Manager – Healthcare Polymer | Up to $10,000",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Title:</strong> Regional Segment Manager – Healthcare Polymer<br /><strong>Location:</strong> Taiseng<br /><strong>Salary:</strong> $8,000 – $10,000/month<br /><strong>Working Hours:</strong> Monday to Friday, 8:30am – 5:30pm (Flexible arrangement: 3 days in office, 2 days remote after confirmation)<br /><strong>Travel:</strong> ~25% APAC region</p><h2><strong>About the Role</strong></h2><p>We are seeking a <strong>Regional Segment Manager – Healthcare Polymer</strong> to lead and grow the healthcare polymer business across the APAC region.</p><h2><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Develop and execute <strong>regional sales strategies</strong> for healthcare polymer products.</p></li><li><p>Identify and pursue <strong>new business opportunities</strong> across the APAC region.</p></li><li><p>Maintain and strengthen relationships with <strong>key customers and partners</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with internal teams, including sales and customer service, to ensure <strong>excellent customer experience</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Monitor market trends, competitor activity, and regulatory requirements to support <strong>business decisions</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Achieve <strong>sales targets and KPIs</strong>, contributing to overall business growth.</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Requirements</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Proven experience in <strong>sales, business development, or account management</strong> within the <strong>polymer or chemical industry</strong>, preferably healthcare-related.</p></li><li><p>Strong <strong>commercial acumen</strong> and ability to manage <strong>regional accounts</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Willingness to travel <strong>25% within APAC</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Excellent <strong>communication, negotiation, and presentation skills</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Self-motivated and capable of <strong>working independently</strong> with minimal supervision.</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Benefits</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Competitive <strong>fixed and variable bonus</strong> (AWS 1 month; 0–4 months depending on performance)</p></li><li><p><strong>Car allowance</strong> (if owning a car)</p></li><li><p><strong>Medical benefits:</strong> 14 days outpatient sick leave, 60 days hospital leave</p></li><li><p><strong>Insurance:</strong> Medical and travel insurance</p></li><li><p><strong>Annual leave:</strong> 14 days</p></li><li><p><strong>Gym membership</strong></p></li><li><p>Flexible work arrangement after confirmation<br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>📩 Apply Now</strong></p><p>Send your resume (MS Word format) to:</p><p>📱 WhatsApp / Telegram: <a href=\"tel:8509 0409\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">8509 0409</a><br /></p><p>Please include your availability, notice period and expected salary in your application.</p><p><em>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</em><br /></p><p>—</p><p>Annie Hoang (R25158747)</p><p>CREW by HRnet | HRnet Ventures Pte Ltd </p><p>EA24C2435</p>",
